  "title": "IT Project Manager (Infrastructure) - Permanent Role",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Lead IT infrastructure projects, ensuring timely delivery within scope and budget.</li><li>Oversee the design, implementation, and maintenance of systems including servers, networks, storage, and cloud solutions.</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define project requirements and deliverables.</li><li>Develop and maintain project plans, schedules, and risk assessments.</li><li>Provide technical guidance to ensure infrastructure solutions align with organizational standards.</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve complex infrastructure issues.</li><li>Ensure compliance with security policies and industry standards.</li><li>Manage vendor relationships, procurement, and contract negotiations.</li><li>Mentor and lead technical teams.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, IT, or related field.</li><li>Proven experience in IT infrastructure project management or technical leadership.</li><li>Strong knowledge of infrastructure systems, virtualization (e.g., VMware, Hyper-V), networking, cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure), and storage.</li><li>Proficiency in project management methodologies (e.g., Agile, Waterfall) and tools (e.g., Microsoft Project, Jira).</li><li>Excellent leadership, communication, and stakeholder management skills.</li><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.</li><li>Experience in budget management and risk assessment.</li><li>Certifications such as PMP, ITIL, or cloud certifications (e.g., AWS, Azure) are a plus.</li></ul><p><strong>(EA Reg No: 20C0312)</strong><br />Please email a copy of your detailed resume to<strong> abegail@talentsis.com.sg </strong>for immediate processing.<br />Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
